        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/thawab-al-amal:2:249:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/249/2",
        "text": [
          ": مَنْ قَرَأَ إِنَّا أَنْزَلْنَاهُ فِی فَرِیضَهٍ مِنْ فَرَائِضِ اللَّهِ نَادَی مُنَادٍ یَا عَبْدَ اللَّهِ غَفَرَ اللَّهُ لَکَ مَا مَضَی فَاسْتَأْنِفِ الْعَمَلَ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
            "2. And from the previous chain from al-Hassan from his father al-Hussain b. Abi al-’Ala from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: “Whoever recites it in his obligatory prayers Allah makes an announcer to announce: O servant of Allah all your past sins have been forgiven; now you pay attention to your deeds.”"
          ]
        }
      }
